<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="122" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,491,698,724]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—This species is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[847,918,698,724]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[930,1043,698,724]" name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1055,1145,698,724]" name="Guyana" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, French 
<collectingCountry box="[1242,1332,698,724]" name="Guyana" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1344,1451,698,724]" name="Suriname" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Suriname</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[187,302,734,760]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Soderstrom, T. S. &amp; Zuloaga, F. O." box="[320,656,734,760]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref26650" refString="Soderstrom, T. S. &amp; Zuloaga, F. O. (1989) A Revision of the genus Olyra and the New Segregate Genus Parodiolyra (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Olyreae). Smithsonian Contribution to Botany 69: 1 - 83." type="journal article" year="1989">Soderstrom &amp; Zuloaga 1989</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[713,784,734,760]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, it is registered in the North (AC, AM, AP, PA and RR), Central-West (MT) and Northeast (MA) regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Oliveira, I. L. C. &amp; Oliveira, R. P. &amp; Carvalho, M. L. S." box="[709,955,770,796]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" pagination="2020" refId="ref26013" refString="Oliveira, I. L. C., Oliveira, R. P. &amp; Carvalho, M. L. S. (2020 c) Parodiolyra In: Flora do Brasil 2020, Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 13423 (accessed 9 October 2021)." type="book chapter" year="2020">
Oliveira 
<emphasis box="[812,872,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">et al.</emphasis>
2020c
</bibRefCitation>
). It grows in open areas, sandy slopes and mountain ranges from 
<quantity box="[395,540,806,833]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" unit="m" value="350.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="100.0">100 to 600m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Soderstrom, T. S. &amp; Zuloaga, F. O." box="[556,886,806,832]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref26650" refString="Soderstrom, T. S. &amp; Zuloaga, F. O. (1989) A Revision of the genus Olyra and the New Segregate Genus Parodiolyra (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Olyreae). Smithsonian Contribution to Botany 69: 1 - 83." type="journal article" year="1989">Soderstrom &amp; Zuloaga 1989</bibRefCitation>
). In the Serra do Cachimbo it was found in Open ombrophilous forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="122" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[136,1452,158,977]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,328,878,904]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Comments:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soderstrom &amp; Zuloaga" authorityYear="1989" baseAuthorityName="Pilger 1930:" baseAuthorityYear="1049" box="[356,641,878,904]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Parodiolyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="luetzelburgii">
<emphasis box="[356,641,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Parodiolyra luetzelburgii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the blade margins long-ciliate and male spikelets lanceolate and hispid. To differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName box="[646,862,914,940]" class="Arachnida" family="Cryptogeobiidae" genus="Taquara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micrantha">
<emphasis box="[646,862,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">Taquara micrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kunth in 
<bibRefCitation author="Humboldt, F. W. H. A. &amp; Bonpland, A. J. A. &amp; Kunth, K. S." box="[983,1279,914,941]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" refId="ref24547" refString="Humboldt, F. W. H. A., Bonpland, A. J. A. &amp; Kunth, K. S. (1815) Nova genera et species plantarum. Librariae Graeco-Latino-Germanicae, Lutetia Parisiorum, 302 pp." type="book" year="1815">
Humboldt 
<emphasis box="[1103,1159,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">et al.</emphasis>
1815: 160
</bibRefCitation>
) I.L.C.Oliveira &amp; R.P.Oliveira in 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliveira, I. L. C. &amp; Matos, A. O. &amp; Silva, C. &amp; Carvalho, M. L. S. &amp; Tyrrell, C. D. &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Oliveira, R. P." box="[338,632,950,976]" pageId="23" pageNumber="122" pagination="61 - 81" refId="ref25821" refString="Oliveira, I. L. C., Matos, A. O., Silva, C., Carvalho, M. L. S., Tyrrell, C. D., Clark, L. G. &amp; Oliveira, R. P. (2020 a) Delving deeper into the phylogenetics of the herbaceous bamboos (Poaceae, Bambusoideae, Olyreae): evaluation of generic boundaries within the Parodiolyra / Raddiella clade uncovers a new genus. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 192: 61 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / botlinnean / boz 049" type="journal article" year="2020">
Oliveira 
<emphasis box="[436,493,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="122">et al.</emphasis>
(2020a: 78)
</bibRefCitation>
, see the comments under that species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
